The paper proposes a novel automatic method for determining left ventricular coverage from cardiac magnetic resonance (CMR) images using Fisher-discriminative three-dimensional (FD3D) convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This involves image processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging and analysis, which could fall under the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses data from the UK Biobank study, which is a large-scale biomedical database, indicating a potential fit for the bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category.
